The multi-agency approach adopted to fight terror after the Westgate and Garissa University raids led to reduced attacks, National Counter Terrorism Centre director Martin Kimani said yesterday. There has been large-scale strengthening of national security system, especially in combating terrorism, he said. “Terrorism organisations like al Shabaab continue to target our people with a limited degree of success, because we have become more effective in detecting and disrupting their plans,” Kimani said. He spoke during the opening of a three-day Global Counter Terrorism Forum conference at a Nairobi hotel. Click here for the latest political news